Can I Unenroll From Medicare ?
You can disenroll from Medicare but consider the downside before doing so . If you disenroll from Medicare Part B and later decide to re-enroll you may have to pay a late enrollment penalty . The LEP is 10 % per year for every year you are not enrolled in Part B . If you disenroll from Part A you may also forfeit your Social Security benefits .
