Do You Need To Have Homeowners Insurance In Alaska ?
Homeowner insurance in any state is mandatory if you have a mortgage but is optional if you do n't . The mortgage company wants to protect their interest in the home by making the homeowner purchase homeowner insurance . Everyone should consider purchasing it to protect your investment and the contents of the home plus your personal liability as the owner of the property . Talk to a local agent and review your specific needs for this type of policy .
Life insurance is regulated by the state of Alaska . The Division of Insurance is part of the Alaska Department of Commerce , Community , and Economic Development . The role of the Division of Insurance is to regulate the insurance industry to protect Alaskan consumers . Bret S. Kolb is the current director .
Auto insurers price their products based on risk profiles that they like and can vary by geographic areas as precise as zip codes . For this reason , it 's not possible to declare on auto insurer as the cheapest in as broad a geographic territory as the entire state of Alaska . You should seek out the assistance of an agent licensed in Alaska who can compare various car insurance quotes for you .
