To be licensed in Tennessee requires 32 hours of classroom study or an online equivalent . There are several companies to choose from . You will need to be finger printed and pass a background check free of felonies , theft and violence . Then you must pass a written exam at a designated testing facility located in all of the metropolitan areas of the state . I recommend taking your health exam at the same time in order to cross license in other states . Good luck !
